The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques for social relationship recognition in still images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel dual-glance model that uses attention mechanisms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also provides benchmark results, which suggests that it falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of social relationships in daily life, which suggests that it falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses a dataset of images, which suggests that it falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
